+# Software Test Description (STD)
+
+## Feature: VMI Hard Reset (Force Reset)
+
+**STP Reference:** [stps/3.md](/home/fedora/thesis/stps/3.md)
+**Jira ID:** [VIRTSTRAT-357](https://issues.redhat.com/browse/VIRTSTRAT-357)
+**Generated:** 2026-02-22
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+This STD covers the Force/Hard Reset feature for VirtualMachineInstance objects in OpenShift Virtualization. Tests verify that a running VMI can be reset via the subresource API and via `virtctl reset`, that the reset preserves pod assignment and VMI UID, that the guest actually reboots (boot time changes), that RBAC permissions are enforced, and that reset fails gracefully on non-running, paused, and non-existent VMIs.
+
+Test scenarios are organized into four files:
+
+1. **test_vmi_hard_reset.py** - Core API reset tests (pod preservation, UID stability, boot time change)
+2. **test_virtctl_reset.py** - Reset via virtctl CLI command
+3. **test_vmi_reset_negative.py** - Negative tests for error handling on invalid reset targets
+4. **test_vmi_reset_rbac.py** - RBAC permission enforcement for reset operations
+
+---
+
+## Test Files
+
